liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Donald Trump will not seek to move a criminal case alleging he conspired to reverse his 2020 presidential election loss in Georgia from state to federal court, his lawyers have said. The development could simplify the former US president's path to trial. Trump, the frontrunner for the 2024 Republican presidential nomination, and 18 others are charged with pressuring Georgia election officials to overturn his loss in the state to Democratic President Joe Biden in 2020. Trump and his co-defendants have denied wrongdoing and pleaded not guilty.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Breaking: Trump will not seek to move his Georgia case to federal court

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Britain's Sycamore Gap tree, a much-loved landmark whose dramatic silhouette featured in a Hollywood movie and was photographed by tourists from around the world, was cut down overnight in what police called a "deliberate act of vandalism". Police said they had arrested a 16-year-old male in connection with the felling of the statuesque sycamore in northern England, which is set in a natural dip in the otherwise treeless, sweeping landscape alongside Hadrian's Wall. It was also known as the 'Robin Hood Tree' after featuring in the 1991 film Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves. Photographs showed the tree, estimated to be hundreds of years old and voted "English Tree of the Year" in 2016, lying on its side across the wall next to a freshly cut stump. "This is a world-renowned landmark and the events of today have caused significant shock, sadness and anger throughout the local community and beyond," said Superintendent Kevin Waring, of Northumbria Police. "An investigation was immediately launched following this vandalism, and this afternoon we have arrested one suspect in connection with our enquiries." The National Trust, who look after the site alongside Northumberland National Park, said it was "shocked and desperately saddened", while local lawmaker Guy Opperman said everyone was "bereft". "This is criminal damage and an attack on one of the nation's most famous trees," Opperman said on social media.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Britain's Sycamore Gap tree felled in 'deliberate act of vandalism'

props.alt: Workers stand near the freshly cut tree, laying on its side.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Here's more from North America correspondent Carrington Clarke. The Republican-controlled House of Representatives has started an inquiry into whether they should impeach the US president. Political enemies of the President have continued to claim they have evidence linking him to his son's overseas business deals. But Democrat Jamie Raskin says the Republicans have failed to turn up any evidence against the president. "If the Republicans had a smoking gun or even a dripping water pistol, they would be presenting it today." A US president can be forced from office if he is impeached by the House of Representatives and then convicted by two-thirds of the Senate.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: An impeachment inquiry against US President Joe Biden has started in Congress
